#X obj 331 844 else/out~;
#X text 604 175 As already mentioned \, we don't bother with V/oct \, so the frequency input for thre VCO module is in MIDI., f 25;
#X text 604 108 Here's a subtractive synth patch with MERDA modules. A very simple example., f 25;
#X text 604 259 Nonetheless \, the signal inputs are considered 'CV' input and it modulates the value of corresponding parameters., f 25;
#X text 604 339 Let's take as an example the cutoff modulation input. As a CV control \, it expects values in Pd's audio output range (from -1 to 1)., f 25;
#X text 604 437 The modulation occurs on top of the cutoff value set in the knob and the amount of CV modulation depends on the knob that sets attenuation (named 'attenuverter' as it also invertes the modulation value if set from 12 o'clock position to counterclockwise)., f 25;
#X text 604 604 The output of the ADSR module controls the CV input in the filter cutoff \, and the output value is from 0 to 1!, f 25;
#X text 604 683 This ADSR output is also fed into the CV control of the VCA module \, so it also controls the amplitude., f 25;
#X obj 67 8 keymap;
